gobblin.data.management.version.finder

Class DatePartitionHiveVersionFinder

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.data.management.version.finder.AbstractHiveDatasetVersionFinder
      • gobblin.data.management.version.finder.DatePartitionHiveVersionFinder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    VersionFinder<HiveDatasetVersion>

    public class DatePartitionHiveVersionFinder
extends AbstractHiveDatasetVersionFinder
    A Hive Partition finder where the the version is the partition value.

    The hive table needs to be date partitioned by prop value "hive.partition.key.name". The value of this key must be a date pattern as per prop value "hive.partition.value.datetime.pattern".

    E.g if the hive partition is datepartition=2016-01-10-22/field1=f1Value. The "hive.partition.key.name"=datepartiton and "hive.partition.value.datetime.pattern"=yyyy-MM-dd-HH
